as, C.D., Hanski, I., Metapopulation dynamics in changing environments: Butterfly responses to habitat and climate change (2004) Ecology, Genetics and Evolution of Metapopulations, pp. 489-514. , In: (eds Hanski I, Gaggiotti OE), Elsevier Academic Press, Amsterdam; Turchin, P., Odendaal, F.J., Rausher, M.D., Quantifying insect movement in the field (1991) Environmental Entomology, 20, pp. 955-963; Vanschoenwinkel, B., Gielen, S., Seaman, M., Brendonck, L., Any way the wind blows -frequent wind dispersal drives species sorting in ephemeral aquatic communities (2008) Oikos, 117, pp. 125-134; Venables, W.N., Ripley, B.D., (2002) Modern Applied Statistics With S, , 4th edn. Springer, New York; Walther, G.R., Post, E., Convey, P., Ecological responses to recent climate change (2002) Nature, 416, pp. 389-395; Warren, M.S., Hill, J.K., Thomas, J.A., Rapid responses of British butterflies to opposing forces of climate and habitat change (2001) Nature, 414, pp. 65-69; Wilson, R.J., Gutiérrez, D., Gutiérrez, J., Martínez, D., Agudo, R., Monserrat, V.J., Changes to the elevational limits and extent of species ranges associated with climate change (2006) Ecology Letters, 8, pp. 1138-1146; Zar, J.H., (1999) Biostatistical Analysis, , 4th edn. Prentice-Hall, London; Zhang, X., Zwiers, F.W., Hegeri, G.C., Detection of human influence on twentieth-century precipitation trends (2007) Nature, 448, pp. 461-466","Altermatt, F.; Zoologisches Institut, Universität Basel, Vesalgasse 1, CH-4051 Basel, Switzerland; email: florian.altermatt@unibas.ch",,,,,,,,13541013,,,,"English","Global Change Biol.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-43349084774
